A Dutch national accused of defiling three girls in 2006 has been arrested in Kasarani. Hans Egon Dieter Vriens has been on the run for two years after defiling the girls aged 8,9 and 10. DPP Noordin Haji said the suspect was arrested by detectives from the Child Protection Unit &Transnational Organized Crime Unit. “Hans Egon Dieter Vriens, a Dutch national, who defiled three girls aged 8, 9 & 10years in 2016 and disappeared for 2 years, was arrested today in Kasarani,” Haji said via Twitter. He will be arraigned tomorrow. Click here for the latest political news